						               													<description>The box includes: 125 triangular plastic tiles in 5 colours with values 1 to 5; 64 cardboard goal tiles (8 x 6 different types of increasing values); 5 dice (one for each color with numbers 1 to 5 and one star) and 4 game boards, one for each player.&amp;#10;Each of the game boards shows 3 empty pentagons (composed of 5 triangles each).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game each player chooses 3 goal tile and puts them on his board under the empty pentagons..&amp;#10;At his turn the player throw the dice, gets the correspoding triangular tiles and places them on his board trying to complete his goals, Unused tile are placed back in the reserve.&amp;#10;When one goal is reached the player keeps the goal tile, gives back the triangles and takes a new goal tile.&amp;#10;The game cannot end before someone has collected at least five goal tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal of the game is to score more points than the other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
